sudo apt install gnuplot

In VS Code:
Extensions -> Gnuplot (from mammothb) + Gnuplot (from Mario Schwalbe)

What to do if you encounter a similar message after runnig a plot test:

qt.qpa.plugin: Could not find the Qt platform plugin "wayland" in ""
/usr/lib/gnuplot/gnuplot_qt: symbol lookup error: /snap/core20/current/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libpthread.so.0: undefined symbol: __libc_pthread_init, version GLIBC_PRIVATE

Try the following command in VS Code:
unset GTK_PATH
